## Early game

**Apollodorus** on Mercury (Survival) is one of the best Ferrite spots at any
gear level — the wiki calls it "probably one of the best ways to farm
Ferrite," citing over 4,000 per 10-minute rotation. Ferrite has no enemy drop
table at all, so every bit of that comes from breaking the containers and
lockers scattered through the Grineer Asteroid tileset; running Master Thief
and popping every locker on the way to extraction matters more than kill
speed. **M Prime** (Extermination), also on Mercury, is a quick secondary stop
when you just need a fast top-up.

## Mid & late game

Once Steel Path is unlocked, **Tikal** on Earth (Dark Sector Excavation) is a
strong endgame spot: a long Excavation run cracks open far more cryo-pods,
crates and lockers per hour than resetting short missions. Because Ferrite
only comes from containers rather than an enemy drop table, Resource Drop
Boosters and the Steel Path resource-drop passive don't change the odds per
container — the gain here is purely mission length and thoroughness, so
squads that split up and loot everything benefit the most.

